genresAdvancedInfo.name: western ny metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This heavy metal subgenre from western New York is known for its aggressive sound and dark, often satanic themes. It features distorted guitars, pounding drums, and growling vocals, and draws inspiration from classic metal bands like Black Sabbath and Slayer. The music often explores themes of death, violence, and the occult.
